definitions.definition: Action given to provide assistance ; aid .
examples: I need some help with my homework.

definitions.definition: Something or someone which provides assistance with a task.
examples: He was a great help to me when I was moving house.

definitions.definition: Documentation provided with computer software that could be accessed using the computer.
examples: I can't find anything in the help about rotating an image.
I've printed out a list of math helps .

definitions.definition: One or more people employed to help in the maintenance of a house or the operation of a farm or enterprise.
examples: The help is coming round this morning to clean.
Most of the hired help is seasonal, for the harvest.

definitions.definition: Correction of deficits, as by psychological counseling or medication or social support or remedial training.
examples: His suicide attempts were a cry for help .
He really needs help in handling customer complaints.
“He’s a real road-rager.” / “Yup, he really needs help , maybe anger management.”

main_definition: ( uncountable ) Action given to provide assistance ; aid .
secondary_definitions: Something or someone which provides assistance with a task.
( computing ) Documentation provided with computer software that could be accessed using the computer.
( usually uncountable ) One or more people employed to help in the maintenance of a house or the operation of a farm or enterprise.
